<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Entity: Configuration  
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration">
A <b>Configuration</b> is the association of a <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_condition_association"/> or a <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_specification_association"/> instance with a design or with a process in order to define a valid usage of it in the context of a certain <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Entity: Configuration  Attribute: configured_element 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.configured_element"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.configured_element">
the element that is controlled for its valid usage by the <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Entity: Configuration  Attribute: is_solution_for 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.is_solution_for"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.is_solution_for">
the characteristic or combination of characteristics for which the instance referenced as the <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.configured_element"/> provides a solution or which is needed to control a process operation. These characteristics are defined by a <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_specification_association"/> and combinations of characteristics are defined by a <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_condition_association"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Entity: Configuration  Attribute: configuration_type 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.configuration_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.configuration_type">
relates to a <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.configuration_kind"/> in order to specify the valid usage of a <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration"/> instance that is applied to the element as <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.configured_element"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Entity: Configuration  Attribute: inheritance_type 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.inheritance_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.inheritance_type">
relates to a <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.configuration_inheritance_types"/> in order to specify whether or not an inheritance scheme for the configuration information in a hierarchical structure is applied to the instance referenced as the <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.configured_element"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Entity: Configuration  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.wr:WR1">
The type of the <b>Configuration</b> instance shall be consistent with the type of the <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_condition_association"/> or <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_specification_association"/> instance for which the first <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration.is_solution_for"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
