  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.type_of_set">
The <b>type_of_set</b> function returns a string which contains the type of the items.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.type_of_set.items">
the instances whose type is consulted.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Function: consistent_configuration_type 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.consistent_configuration_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.consistent_configuration_type">
The <b>consistent_configuration_type</b> function ensures that the type of a <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration"/> instance is consistent with the type of the associated <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_condition_association"/> or <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_specification_association"/> instance.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.consistent_configuration_type.config">
the <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration"/> instance whose type is validated in relation to the type of the <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_condition_association"/> or <express_ref linkend="Product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Class_specification_association"/> instance associated.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_based_configuration_arm  Rule: restrict_to_dated_effectivity 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.restrict_to_dated_effectivity"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.restrict_to_dated_effectivity">
The <b>restrict_to_dated_effectivity</b> rule ensures that effectivity information assigned to an instance of <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration"/> is only of type <express_ref linkend="Effectivity:arm:Effectivity_arm.Dated_effectivity"/>.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Specification_based_configuration_arm.restrict_to_dated_effectivity.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_ref linkend="Effectivity_application:arm:Effectivity_application_arm.Effectivity_assignment"/>, specifying effectivity for a <express_ref linkend="Specification_based_configuration:arm:Specification_based_configuration_arm.Configuration"/>, such that the assigned effectivity is not of type <express_ref linkend="Effectivity:arm:Effectivity_arm.Dated_effectivity"/>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
